<P>> I like what you said stupid, but in addition..

<P>His name is hallarious and you use it with SUCH authority *grins*. The funny thing is that he is anything BUT stupid.
<P>&gt; There are a few things to the faction system that were in my
<BR>&gt; mind obvious, but from reading the above posts, it doesn't seem
<BR>&gt; to be the case.
<P>&gt; Now to expand on it into a more pvp oriented world with guilds..
<BR>&gt; Guilds could have factions that adjust your personal factions.
<P>&gt; e.g. Lets say you are loved by trolls, but your guild has a
<BR>&gt; notorious reputaion in the troll lands for killing huge scores
<BR>&gt; of them, this could negatively affect you to the point where
<BR>&gt; they are dubious about you (seemingly thinking you could be a
<BR>&gt; spy, but they aren't sure :P)
<P>This is a cool idea. It would keep guilds more inline with the evil/good standings and prevent BLUE healers ect. Dunno how they would implement it though.
<P>&gt; I think there are uncountless possibilities how factions can
<BR>&gt; make PvP a whole lot more interesting.. :)
<P>&gt; thoughts and comments are appreciated.
<P>&gt; Ragok Arnskull
<BR>&gt; skull@lvdi.net
<P>I think we agree completey. in fact I have NOT seen a dissenter, thus I dunno why they don't get the faction goin'! (I know I know....they are workin' on it :)
<P>-Gray
